External Knowledge:
- The "total file size" of an asset refers to the sum of the file sizes of all versions of that asset; 
- The "most recent version" of an asset is the version with the latest upload date; 
- The "resolution" refers to the resolution of the most recent version of each asset.

sql:
SELECT 
  MAX(CAST(SUBSTR(file_size, INSTR(file_size, ' ') + 1) AS INTEGER)) AS largest_file_size_bytes
FROM versions;
